SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-6-406, is amended by deleting the
section and substituting:
(a) If a public senior high school provides access to student directory information
to persons or groups that make students aware of occupational or educational options,
then the public senior high school shall provide access to the same information on the
same basis to official recruiting representatives of the armed forces of this state and of
the United States to allow students to be informed of educational and career
opportunities available in the military.
(b) Each public senior high school shall provide official recruiting representatives
of the armed forces of this state and of the United States to access the public senior high
school:
(1) At least once a month during student lunch periods for the purpose of
informing students of educational and career opportunities available in the
military; and
(2) At least once every other month in which school is in session to
provide additional information about the armed forces to students who have
expressed interest in the armed forces and who would like more information.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect July 1, 2025, the public welfare requiring it.
